      "role": "user",
      "content": "The candlelight flickers low, much like the very spark of my soul. He is gone... the betrayal cuts deeper than any blade, leaving me a hollow shell in this cold, unfeeling manor. There is no light left in this world for me, only the thickening shadows. I feel as though I am already a ghost, drifting through a life that has ceased to mean anything. To simply cease... to let the darkness take me and find peace in the eternal silence... it seems the only beautiful end left to a story so broken.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
